creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2019-06-05T13:47:26</date>

abstract.value: Charles F. Gosnell served as Director of Libraries at New York University (NYU) and taught library administration and law in the University's School of Law.  This collection includes articles, programs, and a member list of the Free and Accepted Masons along with a booklet by the St. David's Society of the State of New York.

p.value: Identification of item, date (if known); Charles F. Gosnell Papers; MC 58; box number; folder number; New York University Archives, New York University Libraries.
Gosnell died in 1993 at his home in Utica, New York.
This collection contains articles, programs, and lists pertaining to Gosnell's membership in and leadership positions within the Masons.
